 the farmers work day and night to feed the nation  yet  they  are  unable  even  to  recover  their  cost    the  middlemen  make  the killing    farmers  take  loans  to  raise  crops    a  system  should  be  developed  to provide easy loans to farmers and to enable them to get their loans waived off  the hon  prime  minister  had  promised  to  make  northeast  a  hub  of  organic  farming  each  year  floods  in  assam  wreck  havoc  on  farmers    such  farmers  should  be compensated adequately  every year due to erosion caused by floods hundreds of acres  of  agricultural  land  is  swallowed  by  brahmaputra   unless  and  until  efforts are  made  to  prevent  floods  in  brahmaputra  river  the  farmers  in  assam  will  not progress  in assam farmers are exploited excessively  they are forced to sell their produce at throwaway price  i demand this should be prevented  demonetization also affected farming  loans of farmers should be waived off and they should be provided relief  the condition of tea growers in assam is very pathetic  fisheries can be highly successful in assam  this should be looked into it  efforts  should be made to revive the jute industry    